{"legislative_session": "104th", "identifier": "HB3842", "title": "TOWNSHIP CD-POLICE PROTECTION", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": [], "abstracts": [{"note": "", "abstract": "Amends the Township Code. When the electors in a township in a county with a population of 1,000,000 or more authorize the township board to contract with one or more municipalities in the township or with the county within which the township is located to furnish police protection in the unincorporated area of the township, requires using funds levied under the provisions to furnish the police protection. Provides that a township board's authority to declare the unincorporated area of the township a special police district is to provide and maintain police protection in the unincorporated area of the township. Allows the township board to use the special police district funds levied under the provisions for public safety but prohibits use of those funds for the purchase of red light cameras, speed cameras, or automatic license plate readers. Effective immediately."}], "other_titles": [], "other_identifiers": [], "actions": [{"description": "Filed with the Clerk by Rep. Tracy Katz Muhl", "date": "2025-02-07", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["filing"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "First Reading", "date": "2025-02-18", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Referred to Rules Committee", "date": "2025-02-18", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": [], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "Assigned to Counties & Townships Committee", "date": "2025-03-11", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["referral-committee"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "House Committee Amendment No. 1 Filed with Clerk by Rep. Tracy K